==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ivorytype
<hw>I"vo*ry*type`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Photog.)</fld>
<def>A picture produced by superposing a very light print, rendered
translucent by varnish, and tinted upon the back, upon a stronger print,
so as to give the effect of a photograph in natural colors; -- called
also <altname>hellenotype</altname>.</def> <rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ivry</ent>⟦br⟧
